## 04.4 Logical System Architecture (Technical Breakdown)
This architecture maps our project to the 3-layer design (Presentation, Service, Database), ensuring high performance and data security.

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph "Presentation Layer (Nuxt 3)"
        UI[User Interface & Focus Mode]
        Pinia[Pinia: State Management]
        ChartJS[Chart.js: Data Visualization]
    end

    subgraph "Service Layer (Laravel 11)"
        Sanctum[Laravel Sanctum: Security]
        API[API Controller & Routing]
        
        subgraph "Business Services"
            ScoreSvc[Scoring Service: Weighted Pillars]
            ProgSvc[Program Service: Enrollment Logic]
            RepoSvc[Report Service: Batch PDF Queue]
            RBAC[RBAC: Privilege Filtering]
        end
    end

    subgraph "Database Layer (Data Persistence)"
        MySQL[(MySQL: Core Relational Data)]
        Redis[(Redis: Cache & Job Queues)]
    end

    UI --> Pinia
    UI --> ChartJS
    Pinia --> Sanctum
    Sanctum --> API
    API --> ScoreSvc
    API --> ProgSvc
    API --> RepoSvc
    API --> RBAC
    ScoreSvc --> MySQL
    ProgSvc --> MySQL
    RepoSvc --> Redis
    Redis --> MySQL
```

### Technical Component Breakdown:

1.  **Presentation Layer**:
    *   **User UI**: Provides specialized interfaces for three actors (Admin, SME, Investor).
    *   **Pinia**: Acts as the centralized "Brain," managing identity and assessment state in real-time.
    *   **Chart.js**: Translates backend numeric scores into visual "Spider Charts" and "Risk Matrices."

2.  **Service Layer**:
    *   **Sanctum**: Token-based authentication that secures every API call.
    *   **Business Services**: Decoupled modules that calculate Readiness Scores (Scoring Service) and manage Accelerator cohort logic (Program Service).
    *   **Report Service**: Offloads heavy PDF generation to **background workers** (Redis) to prevent UI lag.

3.  **Database Layer**:
    *   **MySQL**: The "Source of Truth" for all user profiles, assessments, and snapshots.
    *   **Redis**: Enhances performance via session caching and manages the queue for batch report generation.

